President Trump addressed House committee leaders in the Roosevelt Room, commending their efforts to advance the Obamacare repeal-and-replacement legislation. He emphasized the need to act now to save Americans from the failing Obamacare system, citing skyrocketing premiums and diminishing choices for consumers. Trump highlighted key elements of the House repeal-and-replace plan, such as ending Obamacare tax hikes, eliminating the individual mandate, and giving states more flexibility with Medicaid spending. He expressed confidence in the plan's success and thanked the committee leaders for their dedication.